Description:
Some vulnerabilities were reported in Merak Mail Server with IceWarp Web Mail.  A remote user can conduct cross-site scripting attacks.  A remote authenticated user can rename and delete files on the target system.
ShineShadow reported some vulnerabilities in Merak Mail Server in the IceWarp Web Mail (CONTROL service).

It is reported that several scripts do not properly validate user-supplied input, including send.html, attachment.html, and folderitem.html.  A remote user can create a specially crafted URL that, when loaded by a target user, will cause arbitrary scripting code to be executed by the target user's browser. The code will originate from the site running the mail server software and will run in the security context of that site. As a result, the code will be able to access the target user's cookies (including authentication cookies), if any, associated with the site, access data recently submitted by the target user via web form to the site, or take actions on the site acting as the target user. 

http://[target]:32000/mail/send.html?id=[sessionid]&redirectfile=">&lt;script&gt;alert(document.cookie)&lt;/script&gt;
http://[target]:32000/mail/send.html?id=[sessionid]&Old_Folder=">&lt;script&gt;alert(document.cookie)&lt;/script&gt;
http://[target]:32000/mail/send.html?id=[sessionid]&Old_Message=">&lt;script&gt;alert(document.cookie)&lt;/script&gt;
http://[target]:32000/mail/send.html?id=[sessionid]&xwritesentcopy=">&lt;script&gt;alert(document.cookie)&lt;/script&gt;
